{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":707,"text":"So I want to start by offering you\na free no-tech life hack,"},{"time":6129,"text":"and all it requires of you is this:"},{"time":8750,"text":"that you change your posture\nfor two minutes."},{"time":12937,"text":"But before I give it away,\nI want to ask you to right now"},{"time":16361,"text":"do a little audit of your body\nand what you're doing with your body."},{"time":19954,"text":"So how many of you are\nsort of making yourselves smaller?"},{"time":22669,"text":"Maybe you're hunching, crossing your legs,\nmaybe wrapping your ankles."},{"time":26014,"text":"Sometimes we hold onto our arms like this."},{"time":29753,"text":"Sometimes we spread out. (Laughter)"},{"time":33424,"text":"I see you."},{"time":35696,"text":"So I want you to pay attention\nto what you're doing right now."},{"time":38711,"text":"We're going to come back\nto that in a few minutes,"},{"time":41069,"text":"and I'm hoping that if you learn\nto tweak this a little bit,"},{"time":44017,"text":"it could significantly change\nthe way your life unfolds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47453,"text":"So, we're really fascinated\nwith body language,"},{"time":51977,"text":"and we're particularly interested\nin other people's body language."},{"time":55900,"text":"You know, we're interested in,\nlike, you know — (Laughter) —"},{"time":60121,"text":"an awkward interaction, or a smile,"},{"time":64519,"text":"or a contemptuous glance,\nor maybe a very awkward wink,"},{"time":68751,"text":"or maybe even something like a handshake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71989,"text":"Narrator: Here they are\narriving at Number 10."},{"time":75338,"text":"This lucky policeman gets to shake hands\nwith the President of the United States."},{"time":79831,"text":"Here comes the Prime Minister --\nNo. (Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":84758,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":87433,"text":"Amy Cuddy: So a handshake,\nor the lack of a handshake,"},{"time":91140,"text":"can have us talking for weeks\nand weeks and weeks."},{"time":93664,"text":"Even the BBC and The New York Times."},{"time":95804,"text":"So obviously when we think\nabout nonverbal behavior,"},{"time":99755,"text":"or body language -- but we call it\nnonverbals as social scientists --"},{"time":103143,"text":"it's language, so we think\nabout communication."},{"time":106023,"text":"When we think about communication,\nwe think about interactions."},{"time":109050,"text":"So what is your body language\ncommunicating to me?"},{"time":111489,"text":"What's mine communicating to you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":113555,"text":"And there's a lot of reason to believe\nthat this is a valid way to look at this."},{"time":119527,"text":"So social scientists\nhave spent a lot of time"},{"time":121795,"text":"looking at the effects\nof our body language,"},{"time":123900,"text":"or other people's body language,\non judgments."},{"time":126209,"text":"And we make sweeping judgments\nand inferences from body language."},{"time":129648,"text":"And those judgments can predict\nreally meaningful life outcomes"},{"time":133638,"text":"like who we hire or promote,\nwho we ask out on a date."},{"time":137431,"text":"For example, Nalini Ambady,\na researcher at Tufts University,"},{"time":142116,"text":"shows that when people watch\n30-second soundless clips"},{"time":146588,"text":"of real physician-patient interactions,"},{"time":149612,"text":"their judgments\nof the physician's niceness"},{"time":152445,"text":"predict whether or not\nthat physician will be sued."},{"time":155082,"text":"So it doesn't have to do so much"},{"time":156764,"text":"with whether or not that physician\nwas incompetent,"},{"time":159287,"text":"but do we like that person\nand how they interacted?"},{"time":162117,"text":"Even more dramatic,\nAlex Todorov at Princeton"},{"time":165052,"text":"has shown us that judgments\nof political candidates' faces"},{"time":168729,"text":"in just one second predict 70 percent"},{"time":172697,"text":"of U.S. Senate and gubernatorial\nrace outcomes,"},{"time":176547,"text":"and even, let's go digital,"},{"time":178769,"text":"emoticons used well in online negotiations"},{"time":182914,"text":"can lead you to claim more value\nfrom that negotiation."},{"time":185746,"text":"If you use them poorly, bad idea. Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":188969,"text":"So when we think of nonverbals,\nwe think of how we judge others,"},{"time":192066,"text":"how they judge us\nand what the outcomes are."},{"time":194968,"text":"We tend to forget, though,\nthe other audience"},{"time":197088,"text":"that's influenced by our nonverbals,\nand that's ourselves."},{"time":200523,"text":"We are also influenced by our nonverbals,"},{"time":203736,"text":"our thoughts and our feelings\nand our physiology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206099,"text":"So what nonverbals am I talking about?"},{"time":209162,"text":"I'm a social psychologist.\nI study prejudice,"},{"time":212105,"text":"and I teach at a competitive\nbusiness school,"},{"time":214832,"text":"so it was inevitable that I would become\ninterested in power dynamics."},{"time":219316,"text":"I became especially interested\nin nonverbal expressions"},{"time":223128,"text":"of power and dominance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225131,"text":"And what are nonverbal expressions\nof power and dominance?"},{"time":227870,"text":"Well, this is what they are."},{"time":229953,"text":"So in the animal kingdom,\nthey are about expanding."},{"time":232831,"text":"So you make yourself big, you stretch out,"},{"time":235841,"text":"you take up space,\nyou're basically opening up."},{"time":238782,"text":"It's about opening up."},{"time":240728,"text":"And this is true\nacross the animal kingdom."},{"time":243483,"text":"It's not just limited to primates."},{"time":246244,"text":"And humans do the same thing. (Laughter)"},{"time":248952,"text":"So they do this both when they have\npower sort of chronically,"},{"time":252663,"text":"and also when they're feeling\npowerful in the moment."},{"time":255664,"text":"And this one is especially interesting\nbecause it really shows us"},{"time":258736,"text":"how universal and old these\nexpressions of power are."},{"time":262758,"text":"This expression, which is known as pride,"},{"time":265357,"text":"Jessica Tracy has studied."},{"time":267610,"text":"She shows that people\nwho are born with sight"},{"time":270517,"text":"and people who are congenitally\nblind do this"},{"time":273458,"text":"when they win at a physical competition."},{"time":275772,"text":"So when they cross\nthe finish line and they've won,"},{"time":278250,"text":"it doesn't matter if they've never\nseen anyone do it."},{"time":280751,"text":"They do this."},{"time":282068,"text":"So the arms up in the V,\nthe chin is slightly lifted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284590,"text":"What do we do when we feel powerless?"},{"time":286677,"text":"We do exactly the opposite."},{"time":288456,"text":"We close up.\nWe wrap ourselves up."},{"time":290984,"text":"We make ourselves small."},{"time":292352,"text":"We don't want to bump\ninto the person next to us."},{"time":294732,"text":"So again, both animals and humans\ndo the same thing."},{"time":297489,"text":"And this is what happens\nwhen you put together high and low power."},{"time":301469,"text":"So what we tend to\ndo when it comes to power"},{"time":304595,"text":"is that we complement\nthe other's nonverbals."},{"time":307248,"text":"So if someone is being\nreally powerful with us,"},{"time":309679,"text":"we tend to make ourselves smaller.\nWe don't mirror them."},{"time":312323,"text":"We do the opposite of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313937,"text":"So I'm watching this behavior\nin the classroom,"},{"time":317136,"text":"and what do I notice?"},{"time":319673,"text":"I notice that MBA students really exhibit\nthe full range of power nonverbals."},{"time":326926,"text":"So you have people\nwho are like caricatures of alphas,"},{"time":329474,"text":"really coming into the room, they get\nright into the middle of the room"},{"time":332879,"text":"before class even starts,\nlike they really want to occupy space."},{"time":336316,"text":"When they sit down,\nthey're sort of spread out."},{"time":338579,"text":"They raise their hands like this."},{"time":340337,"text":"You have other people\nwho are virtually collapsing"},{"time":342972,"text":"when they come in.\nAs soon they come in, you see it."},{"time":345496,"text":"You see it on their faces\nand their bodies,"},{"time":347789,"text":"and they sit in their chair\nand they make themselves tiny,"},{"time":350607,"text":"and they go like this\nwhen they raise their hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352969,"text":"I notice a couple of things about this."},{"time":354851,"text":"One, you're not going to be surprised."},{"time":356685,"text":"It seems to be related to gender."},{"time":358727,"text":"So women are much more likely\nto do this kind of thing than men."},{"time":364192,"text":"Women feel chronically\nless powerful than men,"},{"time":366778,"text":"so this is not surprising."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368660,"text":"But the other thing I noticed"},{"time":370733,"text":"is that it also seemed\nto be related to the extent"},{"time":373399,"text":"to which the students were participating,\nand how well they were participating."},{"time":377259,"text":"And this is really important\nin the MBA classroom,"},{"time":379841,"text":"because participation\ncounts for half the grade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382522,"text":"So business schools have been struggling\nwith this gender grade gap."},{"time":386995,"text":"You get these equally qualified\nwomen and men coming in"},{"time":390267,"text":"and then you get\nthese differences in grades,"},{"time":392434,"text":"and it seems to be partly\nattributable to participation."},{"time":395523,"text":"So I started to wonder, you know, okay,"},{"time":398546,"text":"so you have these people coming in\nlike this, and they're participating."},{"time":402188,"text":"Is it possible that we could\nget people to fake it"},{"time":404741,"text":"and would it lead them\nto participate more?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":406765,"text":"So my main collaborator\nDana Carney, who's at Berkeley,"},{"time":411378,"text":"and I really wanted to know,\ncan you fake it till you make it?"},{"time":414933,"text":"Like, can you do this\njust for a little while"},{"time":417484,"text":"and actually experience\na behavioral outcome"},{"time":420160,"text":"that makes you seem more powerful?"},{"time":421886,"text":"So we know that our nonverbals\ngovern how other people"},{"time":425338,"text":"think and feel about us.\nThere's a lot of evidence."},{"time":427743,"text":"But our question really was,"},{"time":429189,"text":"do our nonverbals govern\nhow we think and feel about ourselves?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":433253,"text":"There's some evidence that they do."},{"time":435943,"text":"So, for example, we smile\nwhen we feel happy,"},{"time":440579,"text":"but also, when we're forced to smile"},{"time":442757,"text":"by holding a pen in our teeth\nlike this, it makes us feel happy."},{"time":447172,"text":"So it goes both ways."},{"time":449114,"text":"When it comes to power,\nit also goes both ways."},{"time":452920,"text":"So when you feel powerful,"},{"time":455468,"text":"you're more likely to do this,"},{"time":457263,"text":"but it's also possible\nthat when you pretend to be powerful,"},{"time":463465,"text":"you are more likely\nto actually feel powerful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466888,"text":"So the second question\nreally was, you know,"},{"time":469948,"text":"so we know that our minds\nchange our bodies,"},{"time":472531,"text":"but is it also true\nthat our bodies change our minds?"},{"time":476948,"text":"And when I say minds,\nin the case of the powerful,"},{"time":479675,"text":"what am I talking about?"},{"time":481047,"text":"So I'm talking about thoughts and feelings"},{"time":483213,"text":"and the sort of physiological things\nthat make up our thoughts and feelings,"},{"time":486809,"text":"and in my case, that's hormones.\nI look at hormones."},{"time":489876,"text":"So what do the minds of the powerful\nversus the powerless look like?"},{"time":494210,"text":"So powerful people tend to be,\nnot surprisingly,"},{"time":498506,"text":"more assertive and more confident,\nmore optimistic."},{"time":502730,"text":"They actually feel they're going to win\neven at games of chance."},{"time":506040,"text":"They also tend to be able\nto think more abstractly."},{"time":509908,"text":"So there are a lot of differences.\nThey take more risks."},{"time":512552,"text":"There are a lot of differences\nbetween powerful and powerless people."},{"time":515815,"text":"Physiologically,\nthere also are differences"},{"time":518659,"text":"on two key hormones: testosterone,\nwhich is the dominance hormone,"},{"time":522724,"text":"and cortisol, which is the stress hormone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526418,"text":"So what we find is that high-power\nalpha males in primate hierarchies"},{"time":533563,"text":"have high testosterone and low cortisol,"},{"time":536761,"text":"and powerful and effective leaders"},{"time":540287,"text":"also have high testosterone\nand low cortisol."},{"time":542542,"text":"So what does that mean?\nWhen you think about power,"},{"time":544947,"text":"people tended to think\nonly about testosterone,"},{"time":547270,"text":"because that was about dominance."},{"time":549058,"text":"But really, power is also about\nhow you react to stress."},{"time":552528,"text":"So do you want the high-power\nleader that's dominant,"},{"time":555657,"text":"high on testosterone,\nbut really stress reactive?"},{"time":558399,"text":"Probably not, right?"},{"time":559964,"text":"You want the person who's powerful\nand assertive and dominant,"},{"time":563018,"text":"but not very stress reactive,\nthe person who's laid back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566706,"text":"So we know that in primate hierarchies,"},{"time":571856,"text":"if an alpha needs to take over,"},{"time":574948,"text":"if an individual needs to take over\nan alpha role sort of suddenly,"},{"time":579186,"text":"within a few days,\nthat individual's testosterone has gone up"},{"time":582297,"text":"significantly and his cortisol\nhas dropped significantly."},{"time":585802,"text":"So we have this evidence,\nboth that the body can shape"},{"time":588843,"text":"the mind, at least at the facial level,"},{"time":591209,"text":"and also that role changes\ncan shape the mind."},{"time":595338,"text":"So what happens, okay,\nyou take a role change,"},{"time":598120,"text":"what happens if you do that\nat a really minimal level,"},{"time":600704,"text":"like this tiny manipulation,\nthis tiny intervention?"},{"time":603157,"text":"\"For two minutes,\" you say,\n\"I want you to stand like this,"},{"time":605991,"text":"and it's going to make you feel\nmore powerful.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":608551,"text":"So this is what we did."},{"time":611505,"text":"We decided to bring people into the lab\nand run a little experiment,"},{"time":616120,"text":"and these people adopted, for two minutes,"},{"time":619669,"text":"either high-power poses\nor low-power poses,"},{"time":623153,"text":"and I'm just going to show\nyou five of the poses,"},{"time":625494,"text":"although they took on only two."},{"time":627079,"text":"So here's one."},{"time":629809,"text":"A couple more."},{"time":631792,"text":"This one has been dubbed\nthe \"Wonder Woman\" by the media."},{"time":636646,"text":"Here are a couple more."},{"time":637968,"text":"So you can be standing\nor you can be sitting."},{"time":640322,"text":"And here are the low-power poses."},{"time":642307,"text":"So you're folding up,\nyou're making yourself small."},{"time":646644,"text":"This one is very low-power."},{"time":648109,"text":"When you're touching your neck,\nyou're really protecting yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652092,"text":"So this is what happens."},{"time":654207,"text":"They come in, they spit into a vial,"},{"time":656437,"text":"for two minutes, we say,\n\"You need to do this or this.\""},{"time":659610,"text":"They don't look at pictures of the poses."},{"time":661675,"text":"We don't want to prime them\nwith a concept of power."},{"time":664226,"text":"We want them to be feeling power."},{"time":665883,"text":"So two minutes they do this."},{"time":667242,"text":"We then ask them, \"How powerful\ndo you feel?\" on a series of items,"},{"time":670451,"text":"and then we give them\nan opportunity to gamble,"},{"time":672818,"text":"and then we take another saliva sample."},{"time":675583,"text":"That's it. That's the whole experiment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677465,"text":"So this is what we find."},{"time":679050,"text":"Risk tolerance, which is the gambling,"},{"time":680954,"text":"we find that when you are\nin the high-power pose condition,"},{"time":685092,"text":"86 percent of you will gamble."},{"time":687250,"text":"When you're in the low-power\npose condition,"},{"time":689370,"text":"only 60 percent, and that's\na whopping significant difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693370,"text":"Here's what we find on testosterone."},{"time":695850,"text":"From their baseline when they come in,"},{"time":698387,"text":"high-power people experience\nabout a 20-percent increase,"},{"time":701717,"text":"and low-power people experience\nabout a 10-percent decrease."},{"time":706338,"text":"So again, two minutes,\nand you get these changes."},{"time":709155,"text":"Here's what you get on cortisol."},{"time":711156,"text":"High-power people experience\nabout a 25-percent decrease,"},{"time":714954,"text":"and the low-power people experience\nabout a 15-percent increase."},{"time":719086,"text":"So two minutes lead\nto these hormonal changes"},{"time":721818,"text":"that configure your brain"},{"time":723462,"text":"to basically be either assertive,\nconfident and comfortable,"},{"time":727763,"text":"or really stress-reactive,\nand feeling sort of shut down."},{"time":732840,"text":"And we've all had the feeling, right?"},{"time":735627,"text":"So it seems that our nonverbals do govern\nhow we think and feel about ourselves,"},{"time":740835,"text":"so it's not just others,\nbut it's also ourselves."},{"time":743291,"text":"Also, our bodies change our minds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745718,"text":"But the next question, of course,"},{"time":748124,"text":"is, can power posing for a few minutes"},{"time":749968,"text":"really change your life\nin meaningful ways?"},{"time":752029,"text":"This is in the lab, it's this little task,\nit's just a couple of minutes."},{"time":756346,"text":"Where can you actually apply this?"},{"time":758111,"text":"Which we cared about, of course."},{"time":759946,"text":"And so we think where you want to use this\nis evaluative situations,"},{"time":766711,"text":"like social threat situations."},{"time":769188,"text":"Where are you being evaluated,\neither by your friends?"},{"time":771768,"text":"For teenagers,\nit's at the lunchroom table."},{"time":773849,"text":"For some people it's speaking\nat a school board meeting."},{"time":778146,"text":"It might be giving a pitch\nor giving a talk like this"},{"time":781934,"text":"or doing a job interview."},{"time":784732,"text":"We decided that the one\nthat most people could relate to"},{"time":787424,"text":"because most people had been through,\nwas the job interview."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790343,"text":"So we published these findings,"},{"time":793098,"text":"and the media are all over it,"},{"time":794683,"text":"and they say, Okay, so this is what you do"},{"time":796782,"text":"when you go in\nfor the job interview, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":798879,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":799910,"text":"You know, so we were of course\nhorrified, and said,"},{"time":802381,"text":"Oh my God, no,\nthat's not what we meant at all."},{"time":804677,"text":"For numerous reasons, no, don't do that."},{"time":806941,"text":"Again, this is not about you\ntalking to other people."},{"time":809532,"text":"It's you talking to yourself."},{"time":811117,"text":"What do you do before you go\ninto a job interview? You do this."},{"time":814200,"text":"You're sitting down.\nYou're looking at your iPhone --"},{"time":816766,"text":"or your Android, not trying\nto leave anyone out."},{"time":819052,"text":"You're looking at your notes,"},{"time":820946,"text":"you're hunching up, making yourself small,"},{"time":822970,"text":"when really what you should\nbe doing maybe is this,"},{"time":825423,"text":"like, in the bathroom, right?\nDo that. Find two minutes."},{"time":828484,"text":"So that's what we want to test. Okay?"},{"time":830270,"text":"So we bring people into a lab,"},{"time":832088,"text":"and they do either high-\nor low-power poses again,"},{"time":835465,"text":"they go through\na very stressful job interview."},{"time":838097,"text":"It's five minutes long.\nThey are being recorded."},{"time":841713,"text":"They're being judged also,"},{"time":843694,"text":"and the judges are trained\nto give no nonverbal feedback,"},{"time":848199,"text":"so they look like this."},{"time":849985,"text":"Imagine this is the person\ninterviewing you."},{"time":852090,"text":"So for five minutes, nothing,\nand this is worse than being heckled."},{"time":856713,"text":"People hate this."},{"time":858377,"text":"It's what Marianne LaFrance calls\n\"standing in social quicksand.\""},{"time":862117,"text":"So this really spikes your cortisol."},{"time":863926,"text":"So this is the job interview\nwe put them through,"},{"time":866236,"text":"because we really wanted\nto see what happened."},{"time":868457,"text":"We then have these coders look\nat these tapes, four of them."},{"time":871564,"text":"They're blind to the hypothesis.\nThey're blind to the conditions."},{"time":874736,"text":"They have no idea\nwho's been posing in what pose,"},{"time":877521,"text":"and they end up looking\nat these sets of tapes,"},{"time":882611,"text":"and they say,\n\"We want to hire these people,\""},{"time":884783,"text":"all the high-power posers."},{"time":886308,"text":"\"We don't want to hire these people."},{"time":888105,"text":"We also evaluate these people\nmuch more positively overall.\""},{"time":891946,"text":"But what's driving it?"},{"time":893610,"text":"It's not about the content of the speech."},{"time":895626,"text":"It's about the presence\nthat they're bringing to the speech."},{"time":898502,"text":"Because we rate them\non all these variables"},{"time":901003,"text":"related to competence,\nlike, how well-structured is the speech?"},{"time":904566,"text":"How good is it?\nWhat are their qualifications?"},{"time":906824,"text":"No effect on those things.\nThis is what's affected."},{"time":909474,"text":"These kinds of things."},{"time":911197,"text":"People are bringing\ntheir true selves, basically."},{"time":913612,"text":"They're bringing themselves."},{"time":915026,"text":"They bring their ideas, but as themselves,"},{"time":917149,"text":"with no, you know, residue over them."},{"time":919385,"text":"So this is what's driving the effect,\nor mediating the effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924316,"text":"So when I tell people about this,"},{"time":927684,"text":"that our bodies change our minds\nand our minds can change our behavior,"},{"time":931063,"text":"and our behavior can change\nour outcomes, they say to me,"},{"time":933839,"text":"\"It feels fake.\" Right?"},{"time":935406,"text":"So I said, fake it till you make it."},{"time":937308,"text":"It's not me."},{"time":939185,"text":"I don't want to get there\nand then still feel like a fraud."},{"time":942360,"text":"I don't want to feel like an impostor."},{"time":944194,"text":"I don't want to get there only to feel\nlike I'm not supposed to be here."},{"time":948291,"text":"And that really resonated with me,"},{"time":950478,"text":"because I want to tell you\na little story about being an impostor"},{"time":953724,"text":"and feeling like\nI'm not supposed to be here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955946,"text":"When I was 19, I was\nin a really bad car accident."},{"time":958887,"text":"I was thrown out of a car,\nrolled several times."},{"time":962292,"text":"I was thrown from the car."},{"time":964174,"text":"And I woke up in a head injury rehab ward,"},{"time":967162,"text":"and I had been withdrawn from college,"},{"time":969395,"text":"and I learned that my IQ had dropped\nby two standard deviations,"},{"time":975107,"text":"which was very traumatic."},{"time":977695,"text":"I knew my IQ because\nI had identified with being smart,"},{"time":980566,"text":"and I had been called gifted as a child."},{"time":982578,"text":"So I'm taken out of college,\nI keep trying to go back."},{"time":985778,"text":"They say, \"You're not going\nto finish college."},{"time":988002,"text":"Just, you know, there are other\nthings for you to do,"},{"time":990579,"text":"but that's not going to work out for you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":992603,"text":"So I really struggled\nwith this, and I have to say,"},{"time":996161,"text":"having your identity taken\nfrom you, your core identity,"},{"time":998935,"text":"and for me it was being smart,"},{"time":1000794,"text":"having that taken from you,"},{"time":1002457,"text":"there's nothing that leaves you feeling\nmore powerless than that."},{"time":1005580,"text":"So I felt entirely powerless."},{"time":1007383,"text":"I worked and worked, and I got lucky,"},{"time":1009269,"text":"and worked, and got lucky, and worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1011139,"text":"Eventually I graduated from college."},{"time":1013391,"text":"It took me four years\nlonger than my peers,"},{"time":1015415,"text":"and I convinced someone,\nmy angel advisor, Susan Fiske,"},{"time":1019756,"text":"to take me on,\nand so I ended up at Princeton,"},{"time":1022700,"text":"and I was like,\nI am not supposed to be here."},{"time":1025551,"text":"I am an impostor."},{"time":1026845,"text":"And the night before my first-year talk,"},{"time":1028774,"text":"and the first-year talk at Princeton\nis a 20-minute talk to 20 people."},{"time":1032297,"text":"That's it."},{"time":1033499,"text":"I was so afraid of being\nfound out the next day"},{"time":1035986,"text":"that I called her\nand said, \"I'm quitting.\""},{"time":1038799,"text":"She was like, \"You are not quitting,"},{"time":1040655,"text":"because I took a gamble\non you, and you're staying."},{"time":1043213,"text":"You're going to stay, and this is\nwhat you're going to do."},{"time":1046004,"text":"You are going to fake it."},{"time":1047361,"text":"You're going to do every talk\nthat you ever get asked to do."},{"time":1050541,"text":"You're just going to do it\nand do it and do it,"},{"time":1052804,"text":"even if you're terrified\nand just paralyzed"},{"time":1055249,"text":"and having an out-of-body experience,"},{"time":1057622,"text":"until you have this moment where you say,\n'Oh my gosh, I'm doing it."},{"time":1060992,"text":"Like, I have become this.\nI am actually doing this.'\""},{"time":1063958,"text":"So that's what I did."},{"time":1065077,"text":"Five years in grad school,"},{"time":1066485,"text":"a few years, you know,\nI'm at Northwestern,"},{"time":1068609,"text":"I moved to Harvard, I'm at Harvard,"},{"time":1070696,"text":"I'm not really thinking about it anymore,\nbut for a long time I had been thinking,"},{"time":1074696,"text":"\"Not supposed to be here.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076502,"text":"So at the end of my first year at Harvard,"},{"time":1079219,"text":"a student who had not talked\nin class the entire semester,"},{"time":1083544,"text":"who I had said, \"Look, you've gotta\nparticipate or else you're going to fail,\""},{"time":1087235,"text":"came into my office.\nI really didn't know her at all."},{"time":1089783,"text":"She came in totally defeated,\nand she said,"},{"time":1093235,"text":"\"I'm not supposed to be here.\""},{"time":1100111,"text":"And that was the moment for me."},{"time":1102092,"text":"Because two things happened."},{"time":1103708,"text":"One was that I realized,"},{"time":1105002,"text":"oh my gosh,\nI don't feel like that anymore."},{"time":1108136,"text":"I don't feel that anymore,\nbut she does, and I get that feeling."},{"time":1111160,"text":"And the second was,\nshe is supposed to be here!"},{"time":1113455,"text":"Like, she can fake it, she can become it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115432,"text":"So I was like, \"Yes, you are!\nYou are supposed to be here!"},{"time":1118999,"text":"And tomorrow you're going to fake it,"},{"time":1120785,"text":"you're going to make yourself\npowerful, and, you know --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1123498,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1128915,"text":"And you're going to go\ninto the classroom,"},{"time":1132993,"text":"and you are going to give\nthe best comment ever.\""},{"time":1135417,"text":"You know? And she gave\nthe best comment ever,"},{"time":1138422,"text":"and people turned around and were like,"},{"time":1140385,"text":"oh my God, I didn't even notice her\nsitting there. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1143329,"text":"She comes back to me months later,"},{"time":1145146,"text":"and I realized that she had not just\nfaked it till she made it,"},{"time":1148210,"text":"she had actually faked it\ntill she became it."},{"time":1150608,"text":"So she had changed."},{"time":1152431,"text":"And so I want to say to you,\ndon't fake it till you make it."},{"time":1156515,"text":"Fake it till you become it."},{"time":1159312,"text":"Do it enough until you actually\nbecome it and internalize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1162953,"text":"The last thing I'm going\nto leave you with is this."},{"time":1165608,"text":"Tiny tweaks can lead to big changes."},{"time":1170080,"text":"So, this is two minutes."},{"time":1172577,"text":"Two minutes, two minutes, two minutes."},{"time":1174411,"text":"Before you go into the next stressful\nevaluative situation,"},{"time":1177559,"text":"for two minutes, try doing this,\nin the elevator,"},{"time":1180265,"text":"in a bathroom stall, at your desk\nbehind closed doors."},{"time":1183504,"text":"That's what you want to do."},{"time":1184931,"text":"Configure your brain\nto cope the best in that situation."},{"time":1187766,"text":"Get your testosterone up.\nGet your cortisol down."},{"time":1190731,"text":"Don't leave that situation feeling\nlike, oh, I didn't show them who I am."},{"time":1194697,"text":"Leave that situation feeling like,"},{"time":1196421,"text":"I really feel like I got to say\nwho I am and show who I am."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1199417,"text":"So I want to ask you first, you know,\nboth to try power posing,"},{"time":1205208,"text":"and also I want to ask you to share\nthe science, because this is simple."},{"time":1210322,"text":"I don't have ego involved in this.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":1212499,"text":"Give it away. Share it with people,"},{"time":1214286,"text":"because the people who can use it the most"},{"time":1216730,"text":"are the ones with no resources\nand no technology"},{"time":1220105,"text":"and no status and no power."},{"time":1222303,"text":"Give it to them\nbecause they can do it in private."},{"time":1224875,"text":"They need their bodies,\nprivacy and two minutes,"},{"time":1227343,"text":"and it can significantly change\nthe outcomes of their life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1230493,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1231648,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}